    "analysis": "Previous step aggregated node-5 related KPI exceedances by pod and found broad impact: 34 distinct pods had exceedances, with adservice-0, frontend-0, and productcatalogservice pods among the most affected. Many pods show earliest exceedances at or near 08:00, supporting a node-level problem (node-5) that affected many colocated containers. Traces and error_logs point to frontends and downstream services (checkoutservice, productcatalogservice) showing elevated latency/errors starting ~08:00—08:05. To determine the precise root cause reason we need to quantify which node-5 KPI deviated most extremely (largest magnitude breach relative to its global threshold) and when that extreme first occurred. That will tell us whether network, CPU, or memory signals are the predominant anomaly and provide the earliest occurrence timestamp to serve as the root cause occurrence time.",
    "completed": "False",
    "instruction": "Using metric.csv only, focus on kpi_name values that contain the substring 'container.node-5'. For each such kpi_name compute global P95 and P99 using the full series (do NOT filter by time first). Then filter rows to the incident window 2022-03-21 08:00:00 — 2022-03-21 08:30:00 (UTC+8) and for each kpi_name compute: total_points_in_window, count_exceed_p95 (value > P95), count_exceed_p99 (value > P99), earliest_exceed_ts (first timestamp in-window where value > P95 or null), max_value_in_window, and max_over_p95_ratio defined as (max_value_in_window / P95). Also find top_cmdb_id_with_max_value (the cmdb_id row where the max_value_in_window occurred). Return two outputs compactly:\n1) A table of the top 10 kpi_name rows sorted by max_over_p95_ratio descending with columns: kpi_name, p95, p99, total_points_in_window, count_exceed_p95, count_exceed_p99, earliest_exceed_ts, max_value_in_window, max_over_p95_ratio, top_cmdb_id_with_max_value.\n2) A single-row summary giving the overall earliest_exceed_ts across all 'container.node-5' kpi_name exceedances, and the corresponding kpi_name and cmdb_id where that earliest exceedance occurred.\nLimit outputs to these bounds (max 10 rows + 1 summary). Do not return full time series." }

